main event: A witness observed a bright light moving across the sky in Bakersfield, California around 4:30 AM in August 1965.
interesting points: The witness reported a loud noise resembling a propeller-driven aircraft,The object was flying very low at an estimated altitude of 500 feet,Speed estimate of the object was around 125 knots,The object had two very yellow-orange lights shining toward the ground,The sighting lasted for a few minutes before the object disappeared.
sighted object: one unidentified object with yellow-orange lights
witness description: a civilian who reported the sighting
